import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='age', kde=False, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['age'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median Age: {:.2f}'.format(data['age'].median()))
    plt.xlabel('Age')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the age distribution of the deceased?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.countplot(x="gender", data=data, palette="Set2")
    ax.set(xlabel='Gender', ylabel='Count')
    ax.set_title('What is the gender distribution of the deceased?')
    for p in ax.patches:
        ax.annotate('{:.0f}'.format(p.get_height()), (p.get_x()+0.3, p.get_height()+1))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('type').size().reset_index(name='counts')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax.pie(data['counts'], labels=data['type'], autopct='%1.1f%%', startangle=90, colors=sns.color_palette('pastel'))
    ax.axis('equal')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of deaths by type?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))
    sns.scatterplot(x='longitude', y='latitude', data=data, hue='race', palette='Set1')
    plt.title('What is the geographical distribution of the deaths?')
    plt.legend(title='Race', loc='upper right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
